<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1436,464,635]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,500,526]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Prothorax wider than long; sides gradually widening from anterolatero angles to apex of lateral tubercles, which are acute and slightly directed backward; elytra without centrobasal crest; metafemora not surpassing elytral apex in male; femora clavate; metatarsomere I often longer than II and III together. See diagnois of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="White" authorityYear="1855" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anisopodus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Anisopodus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Number of species currently included: 15.
</paragraph>
